## Quick Commands

```bash
# Start development
./dev.sh                          # Backend + Celery (terminal 1)
cd frontend && npm start          # Frontend (terminal 2)

# Hard restart Celery workers (if code not reloading)
pkill -9 -f 'celery -A archive' && ./dev.sh

# Check running terminals
cd /Users/kavon/.cursor/terminals && head -n 10 *.txt

# Database migrations
cd app && pipenv run python manage.py makemigrations
cd app && pipenv run python manage.py migrate

# Tests (always use script — bare manage.py test can hang on interactive DB prompt)
./app/scripts/test.sh                                    # all tests, --keepdb
./app/scripts/test.sh metadata.tests.foo -v 2            # one module
TEST_FRESH=1 ./app/scripts/test.sh metadata.tests.foo    # recreate test DB

# Clear Redis cache
redis-cli -p 6387 FLUSHALL
```

## Communication Style
- Be direct and technical, no excessive praise
- Focus on facts and problem-solving
- Provide objective analysis even if contradicts user assumptions
- Ask clarifying questions when uncertain
- No emojis unless user requests them

---

**For detailed patterns and comprehensive documentation, see the Project Context System in context/ folder**
